author: UGA Sports Communications
title: Sigg, McCoy continue strong play in Nike Invite
text:
Tuesday October 6th, 2015 2:35PM Posted 9:55PM on Monday 5th October 2015 ( 16 hours ago ) Sigg, McCoy continue strong play in Nike Invite photo: Bobby Escoe Related Articles 
PORTLAND, Ore. — The No. 8 Georgia men¹s golf team slipped to sixth place on Monday in the Nike Golf Collegiate Invitational at Pumpkin Ridge Golf Club. 
Fourth after the first day, the Bulldogs finished Monday at 4-under 284, giving them a two-round total of 12-under 560. Wake Forest has the team lead at 546, followed by Southern Cal at 548, Duke at 550, Stanford at 552 and Texas at 559. Georgia is tied for sixth with TCU. 
Junior Greyson Sigg paced the Bulldogs on Monday as he signed for a 4-under 68. Senior Lee McCoy, a Habersham Central graduate, added a 2-under 70, while senior Sepp Straka and junior Jaime Lopez Rivarola each carded a 1-over 73. Sophomore Zach Healy had the Bulldogs¹ drop score of 2-over 74. 
Sigg and McCoy are tied for fifth individually at 7-under 136. Texas¹ Beau Hossler and Duke¹s Max Greyserman share the lead at 10-under 133. 
Healy moved to even-par 143, and Straka and Lopez Rivarola are at 3-over 146. 
The Nike Golf Collegiate Invitational will conclude on Tuesday. Georgia will be paired with Texas and Stanford beginning at 11:50 a.m. Live results can be found at GolfStat.com. Associated Tags : Georgia golf, Lee McCoy © Copyright 2015 AccessWDUN.com
